<br>
Last night, February 2nd, the combined forces of the Karana Council of Guilds under the leadership of Haemish MacClellan invaded Permafrost Keep to slay the fair Lady Vox.  There were a number of interesting things that took place that made this raid so unique.<br>
<br>
-&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The last server split took most if not all of our talented raid leaders and strategists, so Haemish, a Barbarian Warrior whom at the tender age of 39 Seasons, took up the mantle of leadership by organizing and leading this raid.<br>
-&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The final raiding parties consisted of 8 groups ranging in level from 52 at the high end all the way to our lone bard at 37(who was critical in keeping the forward group alive long enough for the nukers to kill Vox).  All in all, the average level was about 46.<br>
-&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The servers went down halfway through the raid – but we regrouped and cleared the castle again for a second push and then launched our attack.<br>
-&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp We did this raid with only 2, yep count em, 2 !!!! clerics (a 51 Vicar and a 40 Cleric) and 1 Bard.<br>
-&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The raiding parties consisted of players from a collection of over 15+ small to medium sized guilds that all belong to the Karana Council of Guilds.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lady Vox was very generous on this raid and dropped the following (sadly no FA books for the Paladins):<br>
<br>
(2) McVaxius’ Horns of War – One defaulted to Merithment 37 of Illuminatus, and the other was won by Edina Elvandar of Haven of Light<br>
<br>
Crystalline Spear – Tanniss Riverwinds - 51 Champion of Forever Knights<br>
<br>
Staff of Forbidden Rites – Drusila (DRU) of Kindred of the Moon<br>
<br>
Warhammer of the Divine Grace – Azuriem Angelgrace – 40 Cleric and Leader of guild Illuminatus<br>
<br>
Tobrin’s Mystic Eyepatch – Morgail D’unistar - 51 Wizard of Fell Omen<br>
<br>
King room loot – Vox Bracers to Salani (47 Warrior) and Crystalline Sword to Cretar (51 Ranger).  With all the talk of Magic and Cold resists – you can imagine how hot and heavy the rolling was for the Vox Bracer &lt;chuckle&gt;.<br>
<br>
We also managed to retrieve 2 Prickly Pears for the Shadowknight Lifeleech spell quest won by Silver Daggers and Fell Omen to be passed down to their respective ranking Shadowknights AND, 2 Blocks of Permafrost – marking the beginning of the epic quests for 2 more of Karana’s Warriors.<br>
<br>
<br>
The KCoG would like to publicly thank Jzonn and Halagar on Ayonae Ro, Steelheart of Avenging Crusaders, Solonel, and Jannelle Alcedonia of Ashborne, and Pippi Langstrump of Silver Daggers all of whom provided the new management team with assistance in planning and execution of the raid.  Your advice and guidance in advance of this raid was the lynchpin of our success.<br>
<br>
The Karana Council of Guilds is a loose alliance of dozens of small to medium size guilds.  The KCoG sponsors a variety of player driven events ranging from player run“Battle-Chess” type chess tournaments in Butcher Block, to low level Tournaments all the way on up to Planes and Dragon raids.  For guilds that are not planes or dragon capable, the KCoG provides a fantastic opportunity for players of sufficient levels in those guilds to experience these large target encounters.  For more information on the KCoG please visit us on the web at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://go.to/karanacouncil.">go.to/karanacouncil.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
