<br>
Just wanted to publicly thank everyone for being so patient and understanding during last night's event.  It was a pretty grueling event lasting far longer than anyone originally planned for - but was totally understandable given the servers coming down midway through the raid.<br>
<br>
This was our first attempt at leading such a raid and will be the first of many.  Over the course of time - we'll refine our organizational methods, and speed up the time of organize/stage/break/buff/raid dramatically.<br>
<br>
One point from last night though - I recieved a number of tells complaining about certain player's attitudes during the raid last night, and I want to emphasize that on future raids, WE WILL HAVE NO COMPUNCTION ABOUT REMOVING YOU FROM THE RAID if that kind of behavior is exhibited again.  The players involved have been given their warnings and I can't impress upon you enough that derisive influences during these raids WILL NOT BE TOLERATED.  Diffuse, don't provoke, Say something constructive or don't say anything at all.  Considering the fact that we all played with people we never met before and were STILL successful - you can't expect a group this size to have the efficiency of uber guilds and planes/dragon capable guilds.<br>
<br>
For the most part everything went well - and considering the fact that the server dumped mid raid - we recovered rather admirably.  I'm sorry the loot at the end of the night took so long - but CR made it tricky - once again - we're refining our organizational methods - so you can expect dramatic decreases in time in the near future.<br>
<br>
With that said - I just wanted to tell everyone what an incredible time I had last night and although long - it was everything I hoped it would be!  My CR and MR resists kept me alive long enough for our incredible Team of Triage Healers to heal me and send me back in.  I only got feared twice, totally resisted about 6 or 7 dragon roars, and after checking logs - noticed that I did at least 'some' damage &lt;chuckle&gt;.<br>
<br>
Malachyte DeLoriel (50 Mage of Guardians of Innoruk) got the kill shot, I think Salani or Manslayer won best Taunt/Battle Cry.  Cassia was awarded to either Nawty or Zeol as grand prize of the night.  Thanks to Lagdalen who's tips throughout the night saved us a lot of headaches.  And MVP of the night without a doubt goes to Verius of Avenging Crusaders whose prescence and contributions as one of 2 clerics was one of the lynchpins of our success last night.<br>
