<br>
We did it like a newborn calf trying to run across a wet field but we did it. ;-) Patience and sleep depravation were pushed almost to the limit but, complaining aside, you have to give it up for everyone who stayed to the end. <br>
<br>
As the KCoG does this more and more it will be more streamlined I'm sure but that is going to require some of us to speak up and offer suggestions of how.<br>
<br>
So, he's my 2cp from the healers end.<br>
<br>
Everything was smooth up until the healing line. Typical raid style, heal your group, assist heal where possible. We were instructed to come up the ramp and all healers were kind of piled in no particular order.<br>
<br>
I heard a /ooc of &quot;here is where the triage will stand&quot; .. but with PC names off all of you quite frankly looked the same. Every part of the ramp was covered so it was anyones guess if the traige was in the right spot.<br>
<br>
The second the first fear wave went off the healing triage was joined by giants and a spider. Happily (?) they all went after our tanks (and Cassia who was trapped between two and I had to heal like crazy to keep from falling) but in the future we need to tend to that little problem.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is to have an appointed Healing Triage Leader. This person will say &quot;stand here, back to the wall, etc.&quot; and basically take some weight off of the raid commander. I felt a great loss of communication on my end and I think this would remedy it rather well. <p>Azuriem Angelgrace<br>
