<br>
I got on right about the time I said we would start, 7:30 pm Central time, and started organizing groups immediately. Luckily I'd made up groups beforehand, and just had to switch people out, mark off those who signed up but didn't attend. Here's where the first thing we need to improve is. I have 2 threads on this board (CoG and Vox) and one for this specific raid. The CoG and Vox thread is to sign up for the MAILING LIST. When the CoG's turn in the dragon rotation begins to get near, I use this mailing list to keep everyone updated on possible times for the raid, all the way up until the day of the raid. In the last email, I inform everyone that they should sign up under the specific date thread to let me get an idea of who is coming. This is essential, you must sign up on the specific date thread (this one was CoG Vox Raid - 2/2). When you let me know you are coming, first off, I give you priority if there are more people than we need. If you sign up, there are only 2 reasons you won't be put in a group over those who didn't sign up: 1) We need more of a specific class, like clerics, 2) You are late and we've already begun. The only time I'm going to let latecomers in is if we need their class (like clerics) or we're at a point where putting you in doesn't endanger us or create too much of a hassle. If we're staging in the king room, I can put you in.... if we're at the buffing line, forget about it. It is your responsibility to get there on time or shortly thereafter, especially for Vox raids, because of the remote location (nearest port is West Karana, a 10-15 minute run from Permafrost). If you have to camp out there the night before, do so, especially if you know you're going to be late. <br>
<br>
After getting the groups made (and thanks to Shoji for taking attendance and Dogedme for giving directions), I sent them into the zone one at a time, and began staging them to certain points so that everyone was not crowded into one area for long. Using 2-3 groups at a time to clear areas ahead worked well, and we were in the king room by 9 pm Central time (or thereabouts). It was camped, so we didn't have to clear it too much (this would have been amazingly easy with the firepower we had). I had invited 2 people to come on the raid that were not 40th level (besides myself), Merithment at level 38? and Draeven at level 36. Draeven had come to clear the king room with others level 35-40, but since no others were available, I asked if he wanted to come along. Knowing he'd probably die, he jumped at the chance. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I may not have this type of thing at the next one, but since we had a group with spaces, and he was there, I figured why not. Casters bound in the king room, and we began to pull ice giants. I made one mistake here, in that after the diplomat was dead, I crowded 2 or 3 groups into his spawn point, as a staging point for taking out the next ice giants. However, that many people meant someone got to close, and we pulled them before we were ready. We managed to get them back into the king room, but we lost 1, Guppin (everyone's favorite halfling rogue). After a quick res, we moved into the second ice giant spawn point (in front of the goblin champion) where we stayed for quite a while. Aere (our only monk at the time, as Tyrin came later) began pulling the ice giants between that spot and Vox's lair. This took a LONG time and cost him a few deaths. This is the part of the night that will take the longest time, as he had to try to pull giants from Vox's lair itself without bringing the big beastie out with him. He aggroed her a few times, had to feign and  camp out. I can just imagine the buckets he was sweating as the great wurm herself stood over him, licking her chops. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Aere did a masterful job, especially on the last ice giant, who had an unhealthy attraction to Vox's tail. This is where we had some grumblers, and some who left from boredom. All I can say to those who left from boredom, you missed a helluva time.... if you wanted to speed it up, you could always try to pull the giant without pulling Vox. You might have had to wait a while for the resses though, as we'd have had to kill Vox before getting your corpse. This part of the raid will get quicker the more practiced we become, and I take my hat off to Aere, he was tireless. As we pulled the last ice giant, we had a big mishap. Chanel pulled the giant, Aere grabbed Vox's aggro to keep her there (sacrficing himself), and the giant was successfully pulled back to us. <br>
<br>
Chanel died, and we had another problem come up. When fighting the giants, you MUST pull them back from the walls. This giant got pushed up against a wall, and through it, disappearing. We looked around, but couldn't see him. At this point, some started suggesting that we camp out, and I applaud those who didn't camp out until I called for it, great discipline. Right after shouting for all to camp out, BLINK, I was summoned by said giant, to a point out of sight of the group. Not knowing where I was and being pounded and summoned by this giant repeatedly, I camped out quickly, and logged on to a secondary. I believe Belce was summoned and killed next, luckily I'd made it out without dying. When I got back in, I was still alive, the giant was dead and I was lost. Luckily I was only a few feet away from the groups and quickly made it back, but the whole time I was frightened that I was in Vox's lair and would soon be summoned by her. After getting back to the group, we reorganized and the second major mishap came up. Verant lost a router somewhere and half of the groups went Linkdead, in a huge Lag wave. This lasted a good 10-15 minutes, many getting back on, then being dropped again. When we finally got this issue taken care of, we reorganized and began the buffing line. Credit goes to Cassia and Shoji for their work with this (obviously they didn't expect it).  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  They got us organized and started... this took a little longer than it should as I tried to go over the strategy in-game. Better to have done so in the chat room later, as I learned. We buffed, camped and thanks to Zeol for setting up the chat room and keeping it open. <br>
<br>
We sat in the chat room, discussed the strategy and then returned to a hot spot. The giants had spawned on us again, and in Vox's lair. This shouldn't happen next time, as: 1) I took extra time to learn how to get to the lair AND where the pit traps were, 2) Tried to explain the strategy in-game. The next time, we probably won't have this problem, or not as much as we did this time. When we got back in, very good timing on getting back in your groups. We had one person reappear at the gate room, who luckily was a monk, as he FD'ed with 4 ice giants spawned around him. Without the ability to go back and get him (as the buffs would wear off) we had to go in without him. I called the charge and in we went!<br>
<br>
All I can say is that chaos and confusion reigned supreme in Vox's lair, yet somehow, somehow the raiders maintained an incredible amount of discipline. I was feared no less than 4 times, and thanks to my DMF buff, I didn't go off into the pit traps (we lost 5 this way I think). The ice giants were fully spawned, yet we managed to get around them and pound on the great wurm. When I returned for my first heal, I found a full set of ice giants raping our triage line. This is what meant my death, as I was healed, then pounded to paste. After reawakening, I began to run back to find out that we had WON! Thanks to all the casters who handled themselves quite admirably, and all the rest who kept killing her. I managed to get a few hits in myself, and my next goal is to actually see most of the battle at a dragon raid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
My magic resist unbuffed was 79, but I think even had it been higher, my level would certainly make me more susceptible. Shoji, 5 levels above me got feared half as much as I, so the lower you are, the higher your resists need to be. <br>
<br>
The ending corpse recovery was complicated by the location, but Aere did a superlative job getting all corpses out of the pits. The loot was incredible, but didn't even hold a candle to the pride I felt at having accomplished the first successful CoG Vox raid. <br>
<br>
My thanks go out to all the raiders, and I want to mention a few in particular. From the management body, I want to thank Cassia and Shoji for the buff lines, loot management, taking attendance, and all the other things they did. Belce for being backup battle commander and showing me the ropes of the dungeon and the Vox raid strategies. Thanks to Eressia, Rbecka, Manslayer, Tanniss, Nawty, Junun, Cassia, Dogedme and Zeol for being excellent group leaders. Thanks to Aronos for keeping me updated on the server status. Thanks to Azuriem, Verius and Iluvatar for being the only clerics on the raid, and quick with resses. Thanks to Talovar (a 56 bard) for trying to get that last ice giant out of Vox's lair and then getting popped to the zone. Thanks to Rbecka who collected and passed out the reagent fund, and to all those who contributed to this fund without complaint. Thanks to Quixler, Cassia and Fazlazen for being our only enchanters on the raid. Thanks again to Aere, Chanel and Shamas for pulling and corpse recovery. And thanks to everyone who stayed for their patience. You all deserve a round of applause and a good 12 hours of sleep... there will be songs sung of your valor. <br>
<br>
Haemish MacLennan<br>
Clan Chieftan<br>
